# CODEOWNERS
#
# GitHub requires reviews from the listed teams/users when a PR
# modifies files matching these patterns. This enforces that
# security-sensitive code paths can't be merged without review
# from someone with domain expertise.
#
# How it works:
#   - GitHub evaluates patterns top-to-bottom, last match wins
#   - Patterns use the same syntax as .gitignore
#   - Teams must be given write access to the repo
#   - Enable "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection
#
# Replace @hawkeyesectest/security-team and @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
# with your actual GitHub team slugs.

# ── DEFAULT ───────────────────────────────────
# Fallback: platform team reviews everything not
# covered by a more specific rule below
*                                   @hawkeyesectest/platform-team

# ── AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION ────────────
# Auth logic is the #1 target for attackers.
# Mistakes here bypass everything else.
**/auth/                            @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/authentication/                  @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/authorization/                   @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/middleware/auth*                  @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/oauth/                           @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/sso/                             @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/jwt*                             @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/permissions/                     @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/rbac/                            @hawkeyesectest/security-team

# ── CRYPTOGRAPHY ──────────────────────────────
# Rolling your own crypto is a common source of
# vulnerabilities. Expert review is essential.
**/crypto/                          @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/encryption/                      @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/signing/                         @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/certificates/                    @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/tls/                             @hawkeyesectest/security-team
**/keys/                            @hawkeyesectest/security-team

# ── ENVIRONMENT & CONFIGURATION ───────────────
# Config files often contain secrets references,
# service URLs, and feature flags that affect security.
.env*                               @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
**/config/                          @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
**/settings/                        @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
*.toml                              @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
*.yaml                              @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
*.yml                               @hawkeyesectest/platform-team

# ── CI/CD WORKFLOWS ──────────────────────────
# Workflows have access to secrets and can deploy
# code. A compromised workflow = compromised production.
.github/                            @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
.github/workflows/                  @hawkeyesectest/security-team

# ── INFRASTRUCTURE AS CODE ────────────────────
# IaC defines network rules, IAM policies, and
# compute configuration. Misconfig = open S3 buckets.
**/terraform/                       @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
**/cloudformation/                  @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
**/pulumi/                          @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
**/k8s/                             @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
**/kubernetes/                      @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
**/helm/                            @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
**/docker-compose*.yml              @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
Dockerfile*                         @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team

# ── SECURITY TOOLING CONFIG ──────────────────
# Changes to security scanner configs could
# silence alerts. Require security team review.
.semgrep/                           @hawkeyesectest/security-team
.gitleaks.toml                      @hawkeyesectest/security-team
.trivyignore                        @hawkeyesectest/security-team
CODEOWNERS                          @hawkeyesectest/security-team

# ── DEPENDENCY MANAGEMENT ────────────────────
# New dependencies expand attack surface.
# Security review catches typosquatting and
# unnecessary transitive dependency chains.
requirements*.txt                   @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
Pipfile*                            @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
pyproject.toml                      @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
poetry.lock                         @hawkeyesectest/security-team @hawkeyesectest/platform-team
